<p>The National Science Foundation-funded Global Names project (Division of Biological Infrastructure, Collaborative Research <%= link_to "#1062387", "http://www.nsf.gov/awardsearch/showAward.do?AwardNumber=1062387", :target => "_blank" %>, <%= link_to "#1062441", "http://www.nsf.gov/awardsearch/showAward.do?AwardNumber=1062441", :target => "_blank" %>, <%= link_to "#1062324", "http://www.nsf.gov/awardsearch/showAward.do?AwardNumber=1062324", :target => "_blank" %>, <%= link_to "#1062378", "http://www.nsf.gov/awardsearch/showAward.do?AwardNumber=1062378", :target => "_blank" %>) is a component of the <%= link_to "Global Names
Architecture", "http://www.globalnames.org" %> - conceived to provide an open and global names-based
infrastructure to index, organize and manage biodiversity data.</p>

<p><em>PostBox</em> is a facility to upload and preview taxonomic checklists in Darwin Core Archive format and is served from the Marine Biological Laboratory. Future versions will include transformation of files into Darwin Core Archive format and validation.</p>

